I have a job = /  was at work, and jumped on the band wagon as soon as the prison that my work let me go home for the day <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START  >D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/grin.gif ALT=" >D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->       <br>
<br>
I have no signature, on any boards, so therefore I have not only complied with their wishes, I have satisfied the hunger of the former FS vultures.  In addition I have learned fabulous volumes of information about copyright infringement.  <br>
<br>
I have attempted to make amends with EQPA for violating their user agreement, and I have removed that which was considered offensive.  I ask that you kindly refrain from additional personal attacks against my character.  <br>
<br>
Some one sent me a tell the other day, and asked me how it felt to be Saryrns most flamed female player.  I guess most days it feels pretty damn special to know that people are so interested in picking apart everything I do.  Other days its, rather burdensome because it makes me think.  Am I really this awful terrible person that people make me out to be?<br>
<br>
So then that leads me to think, do I really care what people like zalf, maneta etc think of me?  Will any of these people impact my life one week from now?  2 weeks?  A year?  The answer is no.  No they won't.<br>
<br>
I can only be true to myself, regardless of what impressions people may have of me.  I can only speak for myself and do what I feel is right with honesty and integrity.  Aha!  A flame opportunity!! Hayley said she was honest and had integrity!<br>
<br>
It has been argued time and again that I don't do the right or fair thing by my guild.  It has been eluded to that I steal from the guild bank.  I find it amazing that the only people making these accusations are those that felt unjustly treated by my decisions.  <br>
<br>
Let's take Zalf for example who doesnt want to pay the 15DKP for the H2H weapon off of AL.  Instead of 1) paying and looting he instead complains incessantly about the injustices of the pricing seeing as though hes the only one there that can use it.   Too bad, it rots.  I am accused of hoarding it for a twink! <br>
<br>
Lets take a long hard look at maneta.  This person whines and cries for days over a dozekar tear that she paid DKP for and wants a refund.  So sorry, so sad.  We all paid 4DKP for our Dozekar tears.  You want to use them, buy a MQ.  I did.  Instead, Maneta cries about the injustices of my decision by refusing to allow her the 4DKP credit.  Her reason?  She lost her DKP advantage and wants to buy things at the Burrower Parasite raid.  <br>
<br>
Am I an awful terrible person for 1) standing by the guild rules with conviction and not allowing this abuse of the system, or am I doing the right and fair thing by asking them to adhere to the rules?  I f asking them to adhere to the standard set forth and imposed upon the guild as a whole, then by all means, indeed, I will be the awful terrible.  <br>
<br>
Does it mean that because you have a bank account over 100K that you are a theif and are automatically stealing from your guild?  Does every guild leader fall under this suspicion?  Perhaps those considering me of theivery should take a hard look at the facts.  1) i share a bank account with 3 people.  Loot that is won in XP groups is split equally among the 3 of us.  Am I stealing from my fuild because I win a roll on an ornate pattern and sell it for profit as opposed to giving it to my guild?  Second, because I am a leader of the guild am I expected to give my droppable loot to the guild?  For that matter is it unjust to ask them to match the 80K offer from someone in another guild?  D and I can 1 group bot minis, that drop runes often.  Some of these spells sell for a fair amount of plat.  As the leader of the guild, do I have a responsibility to give rune spells to the members of my guild even if no one can use, or is not of sufficient level to use?  Or is it fair of me to sell the spells, to buy additional upgrades for myself and or the other 2 people I share an account with?  I can one group Halls of testing.  <br>
<br>
Does this imply that I am a theif for not giving all multi quests to guild members?  Is it not fair to sell multiquests that I have acquired on my own?  With the exception of Vainne, I cannot think of one tavern regular that would say with absolute conviction that they would expect to be able to distribute said lootages as they see fit if not aquired on a guild raid.  Don't get me wrong, I have several pieces of MQ loot avail for the asking.  I gladly and willingly give what I can to my extended family.  <br>
<br>
Where does one really draw the line on an acceptable level for the guild leaders bank account before they are named thieves? Does anyone actually have a concrete example as to how I profited from FS loot?  The answer, in itself is no.  I can think of *one* example of a misunderstanding that occurred that I can think of.  This happened after a Yelinak riad, and the person stated &quot;I wish to purchase the earring form the raid.&quot;  Confused, I said, &quot;For plat you mean?&quot;  Camped to a mule to check a raid target, got distracted and forgot to reply.  That earring now resides on Xariss.  I admit in my distraction, this could have been construed as unfair.  However in tells, the concern and confusion was resolved with the right parties.<br>
<br>
Matter fact, I can think of several examples, where I made it possible for others to purchase upgrades.<br>
<br>
2) FS does not get droppable loot other than just spells.  3) Spells that are acquired at guild raids are either sold to vendors or banked on 1 of 2 guild mules that EVERY officer has access to.  3) any and all droppable loot is rolled on for twinks, or DKP is spent depending upon the number of persons.  4) plat recieved from guild raids goes to pay for pearls, dots, and in many cases needed spells.  Case in point, F07 for a shaman thats no longer with the guild.  However, we did invest 20K to help them buy the spell.  example b) Sunstrike 30K.  Grats Wizard!  <br>
<br>
Let's also keep in mind that Aonodorus keeps many of the valuable spells and loot.  Funeral Pyre comes to mind.  Things like Dain cloaks happen to come to mind.  FS has an abundance of these.  They happen to be lore.  Hmmm lore.  That means 1 per character.  These types of items also happen to reside on guild mules.  Free for the asking for anyone in FS that wants!!  But alas, I dont scream that I have them, so indeed I *must* be a theif!!  <br>
<br>
I think perhaps the people accusing me of theivery are jealous and or bitter that they do not have the player resources available to them to farm said camps repeatedly.  Several people in this game are opportunists, and sieze the opportunity to make money.  Is this only allowed of you do not lead a major guild?  People like Anduran farm tradeskills and make insane profit.  Does TWC expect Anduran to give out said tradeskill product free as opposed to the current market value?  I think not.  Don't get me wrong, Im not saying that I don't share with my guild, I feel I give out much of my resources to better the guild.  I am of the attitude, if we cant afford it, let me help you get it.  All one has to do is ask.<br>
<br>
Seeing as though people are so quick to jump to conclusions, and make accusations because of their own personal feelings of injustice, I can only say this from my heart.  I am human.  I make bad judgement calls.  The signature was a bad judgement call. Maybe sometimes I don't think every decision through, but I am willing to admit that I learn from my mistakes.  In this case, I am really glad that I did learn from my mistakes.  <br>
<br>
No one is perfect, and everyone makes mistakes.  If you feel you dont, take a long hard look, you're likely in denial.<br>
<br>
