<br>
Registered or not the images are the intellectual property of the artist. The artist decides if you can use them and how you can use them. If you admire an artists work enough to want to use it you should respect their wishes in how or if you use it.<br>
<br>
Most of the time it is extremely easy to get away with the theft of intellectual property. Its very difficult if not impossible to keep track of the images. Trust is involved. Artists do what they can to protect themselves but theft will happen. <br>
<br>
The dolling community is very tight knit. They share their work and most dollers can recognize and identify another dollers work. Especially the work of the truly talented. They police themselves and come down hard on people who steal from the artists.<br>
